# ===========================================================================
%NAME Samples1: CSV results
# ===========================================================================
%DESCRIPTION
# ??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????
Simple query executed against VDP, results checked (unordered) against an
external CSV file.

Also, note the files linked from a "%RESULTS" directive with a "[csv]"
qualifier must adhere to the RFC4180 de-facto standard. Specifically, this
standard establishes the comma (,) as a field separator, which might be an
issue for opening such files in Microsoft Excel in non-English locales that
establish the comma as a decimal separator. In such scenarios, Excel will
expect the field separator to be the semi-colon (;).
# ===========================================================================
%EXECUTION[query]
{ ds:vdp }
SELECT first_name,last_name
FROM sakila_actor
WHERE first_name = 'PENELOPE'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%RESULTS[csv] { ordered:no } file:../files/test03.results.csv
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
